cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

The paper focuses on spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which involves signal processing, information theory, and communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves network protocols and algorithms, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper deals with system-level issues and optimization, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses cognitive radio technology and its applications, which could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
